1. Issues are created in github.
2. With the issue's name create a branch: git branch issue-name
3. Is you are in master, to switch to branch: git checkout issue-name
4. When you finish the modifications in your repo according to the issue:
	git add .
	git commit -m 'mesagge related to the issue'
5. Then push the branch to origin: git push origin issue-name
6. Go to github and merge the issue branch. Also, close the issue.
7. To update your local repo:
	git checkout master
	git pull origin master

